1. In a vanilla JS app, at what point in the form submission
   process do you gather all the data from the filled-out form?
   
   A. At the end when the form is submitted


2. In a React app, when do you gather all the data from
   the filled-out form?

    A. In real time as the data fields are changed

3. Which attribute in the form elements (value, name, onChange, etc.)
   should match the property name being held in state for that input?
   
    A. name

4. What's different about a saving the data from a checkbox element
   vs. other form elements?

    A. checkbox elements have their "value" stored in a property called checked. The other elements have their value stored in a property called value

5. How do you watch for a form submit? How can you trigger
   a form submit?

   A. In react you just use a regular old default button element